        <num>CC 2007</num>
        <heading>2007.  Stipulated damages or performance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2007.  Stipulated damages or performance
An obligee may demand either the stipulated damages or performance of the principal obligation, but he may not demand both unless the damages have been stipulated for mere delay.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109263</p>
